<div id="review_100765854" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/100765854" />
    <a title="Rebecca Brothers" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3663595-rebecca-brothers"><img alt="Rebecca Brothers" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1310088743p2/3663595.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/100765854?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rebecca Brothers" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rebecca Brothers" href="/user/show/3663595-rebecca-brothers">Rebecca Brothers</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3663595-rebecca-brothers?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer100765854" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12247301124160489462">Provence is a magical place where the light is orange on everything it touches, lavender and sun flowers fill the fields, and the people walk gruffly through your heart. I was lucky enough to live in Montpellier, France for a month when I was in college. Right outside the town are purple fields and golden roads and the sun, sun, sun is everywhere. Marcel Pagnol was a native of this region and his books capture the heat and the heartaches that this country is steeped in. Both of these books were </span>
  <span id="freeText12247301124160489462" style="display:none">Provence is a magical place where the light is orange on everything it touches, lavender and sun flowers fill the fields, and the people walk gruffly through your heart. I was lucky enough to live in Montpellier, France for a month when I was in college. Right outside the town are purple fields and golden roads and the sun, sun, sun is everywhere. Marcel Pagnol was a native of this region and his books capture the heat and the heartaches that this country is steeped in. Both of these books were made into brilliant films. And this was one of those times a teacher showed us something beautiful and I never got a chance to tell her just how deeply the films affected me. Ms. Diane Jeter, wherever you are, I read these books in French in honor of you. Merci mille fois. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12247301124160489462" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


