        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer342556370" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17367282194598706179">Really admired and enjoyed this one.<br/>My review from when I read it in 2006:<br/>Technically two novels, but the second is a direct sequel to the first and would be a mystery without it, so they&apos;re packaged together and might as well be read as one. (Total is only 440 pages anyway.) When two scoundrels plug up a spring near their farm in rural Provence, hoping to claim it for their own private use later, they start a snowball of events that turn into a life or death matter for pretty much everyone in t</span>
  <span id="freeText17367282194598706179" style="display:none">Really admired and enjoyed this one.<br />My review from when I read it in 2006:<br />Technically two novels, but the second is a direct sequel to the first and would be a mystery without it, so they're packaged together and might as well be read as one. (Total is only 440 pages anyway.) When two scoundrels plug up a spring near their farm in rural Provence, hoping to claim it for their own private use later, they start a snowball of events that turn into a life or death matter for pretty much everyone in the village. A beautiful and relaxing portrait of a slow-paced but hard-working lifestyle--let's walk ten miles daily to get water, but through hills of lavender; with a picnic of bread, sausage, and white wine--and also a great moral story of crime, punishment, love, family, and community.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17367282194598706179" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
