    <a title="Amanda Wilburn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5112530-amanda-wilburn"><img alt="Amanda Wilburn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1617689023p2/5112530.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3250902178?book_show_action=true">May 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amanda Wilburn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amanda Wilburn" href="/user/show/5112530-amanda-wilburn">Amanda Wilburn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3250902178" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9296803816494280807">I was introduced to these books in high school French class when we watched the film versions and I fell in love with the story and these characters. I decided to read this book during COVID-19 lockdown and it was such a good choice for this situation. Not only is the story fantastic, but the writing transports you to this little village and you feel like you’re there. It was a comforting feeling during these times of isolation. Even with the heartbreak of this story, this book (and films) still</span>
  <span id="freeText9296803816494280807" style="display:none">I was introduced to these books in high school French class when we watched the film versions and I fell in love with the story and these characters. I decided to read this book during COVID-19 lockdown and it was such a good choice for this situation. Not only is the story fantastic, but the writing transports you to this little village and you feel like you’re there. It was a comforting feeling during these times of isolation. Even with the heartbreak of this story, this book (and films) still bring me so much comfort and this is truly one of my favorite novels of all time. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9296803816494280807" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

