<div id="review_2915679853" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2915679853" />
    <a title="Kelly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/846465-kelly"><img alt="Kelly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1203896103p2/846465.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2915679853?book_show_action=true">Jul 29, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelly" href="/user/show/846465-kelly">Kelly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2915679853" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5398610994937565173">I read the first of the two novels and will read Manon of the Springs at a later date. I unexpectedly enjoyed this read, but I always have difficulty reading something when the characters are consistently so hateful toward others. It becomes draining. But the writing made me feel like I was a fly on the wall seeing the events unfold and traipsing through the countryside.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


